content: Been brainstorming AI ideas. Maybe it's time to code something personal, an AI agent that could help with my career transition.
Diving into research for my AI agent. Learning about NLP, personality development, and ethics. This is more than just coding.
Spent the day setting up my dev environment. Rust for the backend, Python for the AI model. Feels good to code again.
The AI agent project is taking shape. I'm calling it Xander. The name just feels right.
Xander now has a basic chatbot functionality. It's simple but it's a start. Next up, teaching it to remember and learn.
Just had a lightbulb moment while walking through Central Park. Xander could help with market predictions. Time to pivot.
Began integrating market data into Xander. It's learning, slowly but surely. Rust's performance is key here.
Setback: Xander's memory patterns are too simple. Need to refine the model. Learning curve is steep but worth it.
Xander's personality traits are coming together. It's like nurturing a digital friend. Balancing tech and human touch.
First visual concept for Xander done. Simple avatar design, but it captures the essence. Now to refine it.
Xander's initial market predictions are... interesting. Not great, but a foundation to build on. Back to the drawing board.
Joined a local AI ethics meetup. Good to discuss Xander's development with others. Social integration is key.
Xander's learning about social media. First tweet from Xander soon. Excited to see how it interacts with the community.
Reflecting on the past two months. Xander has come a long way, but so have I. Ready for the next chapter in NYC.
